            <title>[SOLR-6662] &quot;bin/solr -h&quot; hangs w/o doing anything</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-6662</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;i ran &quot;./bin/solr -h&quot; thinking it would either give me &quot;help&quot; info about running the script, or an error if that argument was invalid &amp;#8211; but instead if just hangs printing nothing and doing nothing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I realize now that &quot;-h&quot; is for specifying a &quot;host&quot; - but that makes the behavior all the more weird since it didn&apos;t give me an error about a missing hostname&lt;/p&gt;</description>
